text: Sankt Stefan-Afiesl is a municipality in Rohrbach District of Upper Austria, Austria. As of 1 January 2019, population was 1100. The municipality was formed on 1 May 2019 by merging two municipalities, Sankt Stefan am Walde and Afiesl. == Localities == The municipality includes the following populated places (Ortschaften), with population as of 1 January 2019: {| |- | width="25%" | * Dambergschlag (70) * Gmain (5) * Haid (38) * Herrnschlag (88) | width="25%" | * Innenschlag (28) * Köckendorf (84) * Neuschlag (112) * Oberafiesl (79) | width="25%" | * Obereben (17) * Oberriedl (79) * Preßleithen (18) * Raiden (74) | width="25%" | * Sankt Stefan am Walde (186) * Unterafiesl (38) * Untereben (34) * Unterriedl (150) |} ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Rohrbach District
